strnlght@netcom.com (David Sternlight) writes:
> Marc VanHeyningen posts an otherwise sensible message in which he 
> characterizes the protections ripem sites will have as "CYA games." This 
> constitutes both mind reading and the imputation of motives, 
> neither of which can, I think, be supported. 

Well, it's not an unreasonable characterization, even if it's a little blunt.  
These precautions are indeed meant to make sure that the sites (and their 
corporate or educational sponsors) do not get stuck with federal legal 
complications or criminal charges.  If that means they're playing "CYA 
games," so be it.  As long as the posterior is in fact covered :)...



